The United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) is the United Nations’ global development network. It advocates for change and connects countries to knowledge, experience and resources to help people build a better life for themselves. It provides expert advice, training and grants support to developing countries, with increasing emphasis on assistance to the least developed countries. It promotes technical and investment cooperation among nations. Headquartered in New York City, the status of UNDP is that of an executive board within the United Nations General Assembly. The UNDP is funded entirely by voluntary contributions from UN member states. The organization operates in 177 countries, where it works with local governments to meet development challenges and develop local capacity. We are recruiting to fill the position below: Location: Abuja, NigeriaAdditional Category: Democratic Governance and PeacebuildingType of Contract: Individual ContractPost Level: National ConsultantLanguages Required: EnglishDuration of Initial Contract: 12 Working DaysExpected Duration of Assignment: 12 Working Days Background Duties and ResponsibilitiesObjective of Consultancy: Special Task: Outcome/Output Deliverables: Contract Conditions and Payment Management & Reporting: Duration and Venue: Competencies Corporate Competencies: Excellent Interpersonal Skills: Qualification and ExperienceThe candidate for this consultancy must possess; Evaluation Criteria, Language Requirements and Payment Terms: Application Closing Date19th January, 2021. (Midnight New York, USA) The post Consultants, Course Director at United Nations Development Programme (UNDP) appeared first on Jobs in Nigeria – http://jobsinnigeria.careers. Get all the Latest news, Breaking headlines,Sport, Education, Finance, Gists, Jobs, Music/Video, Technology and Top stories in real time in Nigeria and around the world.